Ask HN: Why do surveys ask “Which are you most likely to use?”
text:
This is a common survey question for ads on sites like youtube, tiktok, twitter etc. They will ask, "Which are you most likely to buy next time you are looking for ___" or some variation thereof.

Why do advertisers ask this question? It seems like that data would be fairly easy to determine given all the data they are already tracking.

Ask HN: Project Euler for NLP? & a beginner course?
text:
Hi, I am going to give a small talk tomorrow for some college kids on Natural Language Processing. Its would be nice if I can leave them with a set of simple NLP exercises that they can try to get to learn NLP.

Also, an approachable beginner course that they can learn from on their own without the help of an in person instructor will be something useful for them.

Do you know of any such resources?
